<TITLE> Govt to bring in 100 city buses </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 9 (bdnews24.com)  The government will bring 100 city buses on to the roads on Tuesday, a government press release said Sunday. Prime minister Sheikh Hasina will inaugurate the launching of the buses. The CNG-run buses, to be operated by the state owned Bangladesh Road Transport Corporation, a state-owned entity, were purchased through international tender. The statement says BRTC purchased the buses with a view to ease traffic jam and facilitate public movements. The project is financed by Nordic Development Fund. Communications minister Syed Abul Hossain and roads and railways division secretary Md Mozammel Haque Khan will also attend the ceremony among others, the statement added. bd
